Hello,
Hope everything is well :)

I am developing a OSMDROID map, that contains several points related to Pubs.

And today, regarding the RadiusMarkererCluster, I've found a bug, that I couldn't, yet, figure out a way to solve it.

I have this code:

```java
if (ads.isNotEmpty()) {
                context?.let {
                    val maxIterations = 1000
                    val activeMarkers = mutableListOf<GeoPoint>()
                    var iterations = 0 // counter for limiting loop iterations
                    var offset = 0.0
                    var foundExistingAnnotation = false

                    binding.osmMapView.overlays.remove(adMarker)
                    binding.osmMapView.invalidate()

                    ads?.forEach { ad ->
                        val coordinateToCheckLat = ad.ad.location.latitude
                        val coordinateToCheckLon = ad.ad.location.longitude
                        while (iterations < maxIterations) {
                            for (existingAnnotation in activeMarkers) {
                                if (existingAnnotation.latitude == coordinateToCheckLat && existingAnnotation.longitude == coordinateToCheckLon) {
                                    offset += 1
                                }
                            }

                            if (!foundExistingAnnotation) {
                                break // No existing annotation found, break out of the loop
                            }
                            iterations += 1
                        }

                        if (iterations >= maxIterations) {
                            Container.logger.logNonFatalIssue(Throwable("[Marker Offset] Maximum iterations reached, unable to find a free location"))
                            return
                        }

                        offset += 1
                        val offsetMultiplier = offset * 0.0002
                        val adjustedCoordinate = GeoPoint(
                            coordinateToCheckLat + offsetMultiplier,
                            coordinateToCheckLon
                        )

                        // create and add the marker
                        val marker = Marker(binding.osmMapView)
